📚 Theory Content

Kernels for Non-linear Classification

Kernel	        |    Formula	                      |      Use Case

Linear	        |    $K(x,y) = x^T y$	              |    Linearly separable data

Polynomial	    |    $K(x,y) = (γx^T y + r)^d$	    |      Polynomial boundaries

RBF (Gaussian)	|    $K(x,y) = exp(-γ|x-y|^2)$	    |      Most common, flexible

Sigmoid	        |    $K(x,y) = tanh(γx^T y + r)$	  |      Neural network-like

